        <div style="float:left;width:100%;font-size:16px;font-weight:bold;">
            <p>In order to fulfill its vision to become a healthcare destination for all,Our Hospital established an Outreach Department in 2000 which was initially providing Laboratory Services and over the years it has grown exponentially to become a multi-specialty service, with several collection points catering to over 150 clients across the Pakistan.
               </p>
            <h3>Outreach services include:</h3>
           
            <ul>
                <li>Clinical Laboratories</li>
                <li>Radiology department</li>
                <li>Nuclear Medicine Department</li>
                <li>Cardio-pulmonary Diagnostic Department</li>
                <li>Neurophysiology Diagnostics Department</li>
                <li>The Domiciliary Services of Physiotherapy and Nursing</li>
                </ul>
            <h3>OUTREACH SERVICES OF CLINICAL LABORATORIES:</h3>
            <p>Our Outreach collection points of the laboratory services offer specialised tests along with the routine tests. The following special tests are offered:</p>
             <ul>
                <li>PCR for HBV</li>
                 <li>Herpes Simplex</li>
                 <li>Mycobacterium Tuberculosis</li>
                 <li>Quantitative (Viral Load)</li>
                 <li>Genotyping on HCV</li>
                 <li>Histopathology</li>
                 <li>Tumour Markers on tissue biopsies and bone marrow trephines</li>
                 <li>Flow cytometry</li>
                 <li>Immuno-fluorescence on skin biopsies</li>
                </ul>
            <h3>OUTREACH SERVICES (DOMICILIARY SERVICES) OF OUR PHYSIOTHERAPY DEPARTMENT:</h3>
            <p>Domiciliary Physiotherapy service provides rehabilitation and self- management strategies for the patients within their own accommodations. Our physiotherapy department aims to help people recover their movements as much as possible through teaching and helping the patients to engage in movement, exercise and therapy techniques. We have a highly qualified and trained staff of physiotherapists, who use manual therapy, electrotherapy, exercise and advice to help restore the movement and function when someone is affected by injury, illness or disability. A treatment plan is also formed, based on patient centered goals. We have kept economical charges for the domiciliary physiotherapy, around 800 rupees per session / visit (30 minutes).</p>
